properties.name: Ben Hill Griffin Stadium
properties.description: Posted by Jtener

properties.name: Bryant-Denny Stadium
properties.description: Posted by JtenerThe fans here are noisy and rowdy. They are merciless in shouting profanities and other insults at everyone not wearing crimson. This can be very frightening for opposing fans at times.

properties.name: Cotton Bowl Stadium
properties.description: Posted by JtenerThe Cotton Bowl is one of the oldest venues in college football. The Cotton Bowl Classic is held every New Year\'s Day. During the week prior to the game fans, players, and band members are treated to many luxeries such as a night of bowling, a night at Medievel Times, and the game itself.

properties.name: Georgia Dome
properties.description: Posted by JtenerThe Georgia Dome is usually home to the Atlanta Falcons. Every December it hosts the SEC Championship Game where the participating teams, fans, and bands are treated to an enjoyable weekend capped off by the football game.

properties.name: Liberty Bowl Memorial Stadium
properties.description: Posted by JtenerThe Liberty Bowl is home to the Memphis Tigers. The fans here bark at times but do not bite for the most part. I was hit by a flying water bottle once.

properties.name: Notre Dame Stadium
properties.description: Posted by JtenerOne of the most historic venues in all of college football, Notre Dame boasts some of the nicest fans in the country. They often welcome opposing fans, players, and band members with kind remarks before the game and complements on a job well done after the game.

properties.name: Raymond James Stadium
properties.description: Posted by JtenerRaymond James Stadium is the home of the Tampa Bay Buccaneers. It also hosts the Outback Bowl on New Year\'s Day. Fans, players, and band members are treated to many fun activities such as days at the beach, great restaurants, and other fun activities along the gulf coast.

properties.name: Sanford Stadium
properties.description: Posted by JtenerSanford Stadium has some mean and loud fans. They show no mercy to anyone from the opposing school. They have been known to throw beer bottles at them. They have also been known to say, "Go back to red Tennessee you Commies." Don\'t ask me why.

properties.name: Vanderbilt Stadium
properties.description: Posted by JtenerVanderbilt Stadium is very small compared to most other stadiums in the SEC. For many games the visiting team has more fans there than Vanderbilt does. The fans here are usually very humble for good reason and thus are not very rowdy.

properties.name: Williams Bryce Stadium
properties.description: Posted by JtenerWilliams Bryce Stadium has fans that are relatively tame compared to the rest of the SEC. Although they have been known to throw objects on to the field when displeased with officials. They are really more bark than bite.
